Instruction : 

mkdir project_SST_test
cd project_SST_test
cmsrel CMSSW_11_2_0_pre8
cd src 
cmsenv
git-cms-init 
git pull https://github.com/doujadarej/cmssw SiStripTriplet_AfterPR
git cms-addpkg DQM/TrackingMonitorSource
git cms-addpkg DataFormats/TrackReco
git cms-addpkg RecoParticleFlow/PFTracking
git cms-addpkg RecoTracker
git cms-addpkg Validation/RecoTrack 
git cms-addpkg Configuration/Eras


scramv1 b -j6 

---------

copy step2.root from (generated with runTheMatrix.py 11834.0) :
cp /opt/sbg/cms/ui3_data1/ddarej/AfterPR_SST/CMSSW_11_2_0_pre8/src/11834.0_TTbar_14TeV+2021PU+TTbar_14TeV_TuneCP5_GenSim+DigiPU+RecoPU+HARVESTPU+Nano/step2.root . 

copy step3_trackingPerf.py (generated with runTheMatrix.py 11834.0 and added TrackingNTuple to check quickly the output of algo) 
cp /opt/sbg/cms/ui3_data1/ddarej/AfterPR_SST/CMSSW_11_2_0_pre8/src/11834.0_TTbar_14TeV+2021PU+TTbar_14TeV_TuneCP5_GenSim+DigiPU+RecoPU+HARVESTPU+Nano/step3_trackingNTuple.py . 


and run step3 by doing :
cmsDriver.py step3_trackingNTuple.py 
I advise to run on just 3 events so that its quicker 

to check the algos that work go to trackingNTuple.root > tree_track_algo 
NB : SiStripTriplet is now iteration 25

by default, step3 runs with standard tracking sequence 
for now I let SiStripTriplet in standard sequence and all other sequences, but already wrote modifier "displacedTracking"

----------



Modifier is simply defined in : Configuration/Eras/python/Modifier_displacedTracking_cff.py
IMO, the two files that need to change are :
src/RecoTracker/FinalTrackSelectors/python/earlyGeneralTracks_cfi.py
and 
src/RecoTracker/IterativeTracking/python/iterativeTkConfig.py
maybe others too ?


--------- 
When you want to add the modifier go to step3_trackingNTuple.py, comment the line 10 and uncomment the lines 15 and 16 

to rerun -> cmsDriver.py step3_trackingNTuple.root 
